---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="PEOPB is a Ghanaian technology company founded by Michael Owusu Agyekum, building software African organizations run on."
	path="/about"
>
	<section class="mx-auto max-w-[720px] px-6 pt-16 pb-10">
		<p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-gold-text font-semibold mb-4">
			About
		</p>
		<h1 class="font-display text-4xl leading-[1.1] font-medium text-balance mb-5">
			About PEOPB
		</h1>
		<p class="text-lg text-slate max-w-[60ch]">
			We build the software and intelligent digital solutions African
			organizations run on, starting with the church.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="border-t border-line">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-[720px] px-6 py-12 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 items-start">
			<div class="aspect-square rounded-xl border border-dashed border-line flex items-center justify-center font-mono text-xs text-slate">
				Founder photo
			</div>
			<div class="md:col-span-2">
				<p class="font-semibold text-lg mb-1">Michael Owusu Agyekum</p>
				<p class="text-sm text-slate mb-4">Founder &amp; Technical Lead, Accra, Ghana</p>
				<p class="text-slate">
					PEOPB was registered in 2020, years before Aseda Church Suite, its
					first product, existed. That order matters: PEOPB is a company that
					built a product, not a product wearing a company name.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="border-t border-line">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-[720px] px-6 py-10 flex flex-wrap gap-x-10 gap-y-4">
			<div class="font-mono">
				<div class="text-lg font-semibold tabular-nums">2020-12-02</div>
				<div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-slate">Registered</div>
			</div>
			<div class="font-mono">
				<div class="text-lg font-semibold tabular-nums">BN059661220</div>
				<div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-slate">Registration no.</div>
			</div>
			<div class="font-mono">
				<div class="text-lg font-semibold">Kwabenya</div>
				<div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-slate">Accra, Ghana</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="border-t border-line">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-[720px] px-6 py-14">
			<h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-medium mb-4">Mission</h2>
			<p class="text-slate mb-10 max-w-[60ch]">
				We build the software and intelligent digital solutions African
				organizations run on, starting with the church.
			</p>
			<h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-medium mb-4">Vision</h2>
			<p class="text-slate max-w-[60ch] mb-4">
				Become the technology backbone African organizations depend on.
			</p>
			<p class="text-slate max-w-[60ch]">
				That's a twenty-year bet, not a launch slogan. Decisions here, what
				to build, who to hire, which contracts to take, get made for whether
				they hold up in 2046, not whether they look good this quarter.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="border-t border-line">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-[720px] px-6 py-14">
			<h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-medium mb-4">Engineering philosophy</h2>
			<p class="text-slate max-w-[60ch] mb-4">
				Every product connects to a shared backbone rather than operating as
				a disconnected tool. Guanhwɛfo is the clearest example: the master
				data store every other Aseda Church Suite application reads from,
				not one of several systems that happen to share a name. We'd rather
				build that kind of foundation once than patch five shallow ones.
			</p>
			<p class="text-slate max-w-[60ch]">
				We don't announce what isn't real. Steward and Store are labeled
				Coming Soon because they are, not because "in development" polls
				better than a live product. The same discipline applies to every
				claim on this site: if it can't be checked against the product, the
				registration documents, or the code, it doesn't go here.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="border-t border-line">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-[720px] px-6 py-16 text-center">
			<h2 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium mb-6 text-balance">
				Want to work on this with us?
			</h2>
			<div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
				<a
					href="/careers"
					class="inline-flex items-center text-sm font-semibold rounded-md px-5 py-2.5 border border-line hover:border-ink transition-colors"
				>
					See careers
				</a>
				<a
					href="/contact"
					class="inline-flex items-center text-sm font-semibold rounded-md px-5 py-2.5 bg-ink text-fog hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity"
				>
					Contact us
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
